Data Analysis

cars %>% 
  count(cyl)

## 3     8    14

  count(cyl) %>% 
  print()
## # A tibble: 3 x 2
##     cyl     n

## 2     6     7
## 3     8    14
cars %>% 
  count(cyl, gear)
## # A tibble: 8 x 3
##     cyl  gear     n
##   <int> <int> <int>
## 1     4     3     1
## 2     4     4     8
## 3     4     5     2
## 4     6     3     2
## 5     6     4     4
## 6     6     5     1

## 8     8     5     2
cars %>% 
  summarise(meanmpg = mean(mpg, na.rm = T))
## # A tibble: 1 x 1
##   meanmpg
##     <dbl>
## 1    20.1
cars %>% 
  group_by(cyl) %>% 
  summarise(meanmpg = mean(mpg, na.rm =T))
## # A tibble: 3 x 2
##     cyl meanmpg
##   <int>   <dbl>
## 1     4    26.7
## 2     6    19.7
## 3     8    15.1
cars %>% 
  count(cyl) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=cyl, y=n))+
  geom_col()

cars %>% 
  count(cyl) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=cyl, y=n))+
  geom_abline()

cars %>% 
  count(cyl) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=cyl, y=n))+
  geom_col(fill="#741D5A")+
  labs(y="Number", x= "Cylinders")+
  ggtitle("Number of Cars by Cylinder")+
  theme_minimal()

Create a table of mean mpg by cyl

mpgbycyl <- cars %>% 
  group_by(cyl) %>% 
  summarise(meanmpg = mean(mpg, na.rm = T)) %>% 
  print()
## # A tibble: 3 x 2
##     cyl meanmpg
##   <int>   <dbl>
## 1     4    26.7
## 2     6    19.7
## 3     8    15.1

Graph mean mpg by cyl

mpgbycyl %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = cyl, y = meanmpg))+
  geom_point(color = "#CD5C5C", size =3)+
  labs(title = "Mean mpg by cylinder", x= "No. of cylinders", y="Mean miles per gallon")+
  theme_minimal()

Other exploratory analysis

#mean mpg by carb

mpgbycarb <- cars %>% 
  group_by(carb) %>% 
  summarise(meanmpg = mean(mpg, na.rm = T)) %>% 
  print() #More the number of carburetors, lesser the mpg  
## # A tibble: 6 x 2
##    carb meanmpg
##   <int>   <dbl>
## 1     1    25.3
## 2     2    22.4
## 3     3    16.3
## 4     4    15.8
## 5     6    19.7
## 6     8    15.0
cars %>% 
  group_by(carb,cyl) %>% 
  summarise(meanmpg = mean(mpg, na.rm = T)) %>% 
  print() # For a given number of carburetor, as the number of cylinders increase, mpg decreases
## # A tibble: 9 x 3
## # Groups:   carb [?]
##    carb   cyl meanmpg
##   <int> <int>   <dbl>
## 1     1     4    27.6
## 2     1     6    19.8
## 3     2     4    25.9
## 4     2     8    17.2
## 5     3     8    16.3
## 6     4     6    19.8
## 7     4     8    13.2
## 8     6     6    19.7
## 9     8     8    15.0
cars %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = drat, y = mpg))+
  geom_point(color = "#CD5C5C", size =3)+
  labs(title = "Miles per gallon vs. Rear axle ratio", x = "Rear axle ratio", y = "Miles per gallon")+
  theme_minimal()
